{{Quote|I think that sense that "wisdom" isn't just a vague character trait, but rather the scar tissue left behind after life has kicked the stuffing out of you, was my starting point for writing about Yoda (and Dooku too). You can be many things at 800, but "innocent" isn't really one of them.|Sean Stewart|<ref name="TOS interview">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/novel/f20041203/index.html|text=Rendezvous with Yoda: Six Questions for Sean Stewart}}</ref>}}
'''Sean Stewart''' is an [[Wikipedia:American Canadians|American-Canadian]] author. Stewart made his first entry into the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe with the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] novel ''[[Yoda: Dark Rendezvous]]''.<ref name="Yoda DR" />

According to Stewart, he had been interested in writing a ''Star Wars'' story that started with the phrase "the Force is weak in this one" since he was twelve years old.<ref name="12Years">{{Twitter|username=SStewartWriter|url=status/1592921527804399616|name=[[Sean Stewart]]|date=2022-11-16|quote=So Del Rey is re-issuing my adventure in the galaxy far, far away.  I was 12 when I first thought I wanted to write a story that started at "the Force is weak in this one..."|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/Ng0ZW}}</ref> As he was finishing ''Yoda: Dark Rendezvous'',<ref name="Spartans">{{Twitter|username=SStewartWriter|url=status/1592922914474819584|name=[[Sean Stewart]]|date=2022-11-16|quote=right?  I was finishing this as we were starting I Love Bees, btw, so the fact that both Jedi and Spartans were stolen children really popped. Drove the ending for ILB in some important ways.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/TyoZl}}</ref> specifically two days after he turned it in according to his later recollection,<ref name="TwoDays">{{Twitter|username=SStewartWriter|url=status/1813244136410972668|name=[[Sean Stewart]]|date=2024-07-16|quote=I started writing on ILB literally two days after turning in Yoda: Dark Rendezvous, and was astonished by the parallels between the Spartan and Jedi origin stories.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/LuJaX}}</ref> he moved onto the ''[[Wikipedia:Halo (franchise)|Halo]]'' project ''[[Wikipedia:I Love Bees|I Love Bees]]'', which lead to Stewart drawing links between the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and ''Halo'' Spartans, which affected how he wrote ''I Love Bees''.<ref name="Spartans" /> He was surprised that he was able to find this connection, pointing to the origin story of both groups<ref name="TwoDays" /> in that both [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and Spartians began their new life as children.<ref name="Spartans" />

